# CMD These command-line editing commands are the most helpful for new users. For other commands, refer to the bash(1) man page.
bash(1), date(1), file(1), magic(5), cat(1), more(1), less(1), head(1), passwd(1), tail(1), and wc(1) man pages

# Shortcut	Description
Ctrl+A	Jump to the beginning of the command line.
Ctrl+E	Jump to the end of the command line.
Ctrl+U	Clear from the cursor to the beginning of the command line.
Ctrl+K	Clear from the cursor to the end of the command line.
Ctrl+LeftArrow	Jump to the beginning of the previous word on the command line.
Ctrl+RightArrow	Jump to the end of the next word on the command line.
Ctrl+R	Search the history list of commands for a pattern.

